context:
The George Brown College Government Relations team collaborates with various organizations including Colleges and Institutes Canada (CICAN), Colleges Ontario (CO), and the Ontario Chamber of Commerce (OCC). CICAN is the national and international voice for Canada's largest post-secondary education network, representing publicly supported colleges, institutes, CEGEPs, and polytechnics. CO is the association for Ontario's 24 public colleges, promoting their role in the economy and strengthening the quality of programs. The OCC is an independent non-profit organization with 60,000 members, including postsecondary institutions, advocating for business interests and driving competitiveness and economic growth in the province. Polytechnics Canada represents 13 leading research-intensive polytechnics, colleges, and institutes of technology, focusing on federal action in areas such as Research & Innovation, Skills & Talent, and Diversity & Inclusion.

Entities: Colleges and Institutes Canada (CICAN), Colleges Ontario (CO), Ontario Chamber of Commerce (OCC), Polytechnics Canada.
